For my sanity, I only configure Jetty programmatically.  If you&#39;re looking to change the cookie path in Jetty 11:
```
sessionHandler.getSessionCookieConfig().setPath(&quot;/&quot;);
```
If you&#39;re not explicitly creating SessionHandler, you can get a reference to it after you create things like servlet contexts....
```
ServletContextHandler sch = new ServletContextHandler(..., &quot;/api&quot;, true, false);
sch.getSessionHandler().getSessionCookieConfig().setPath(&quot;/&quot;);
```
This way, even though the context is under `/api` the session cookie can be accessible in other contexts.

